snippet: Part of Anne Teresa de Keersmaeker’s seminal “Rosas danst Rosas,” which she created in 1983, has been replicated by more than 1500 people all over the world, as a part of a project to celebrate the work’s 30th anniversary.

headline.main: De Keersmaeker's Famous 'Rosas' Dance Gets the Fan Treatment
